# Failure Detection Engine

The Failure Detection Engine converts normalized log events into meaningful failure categories.

The detection process is:

```
Raw Logs

   |

   v

Parser

   |

   v

Normalized Events

   |

   v

Pattern Detector

   |

   v

Failure Categories

   |

   v

Root Cause Engine
```

---

# Detection Architecture

The detector layer is intentionally rule-based and extensible.

Current design:

```
src/

└── detector/

    └── pattern_detector.py
```

The detector receives parsed events and evaluates them against known failure signatures.

---

# Event Processing Model

A log entry is converted into a normalized event.

Example:

Input:

```
Jan 01 10:00:01 eth0: link down
```

Normalized event:

```json
{
    "timestamp":
        "10:00:01",

    "category":
        "ETHERNET_FAILURE",

    "severity":
        "ERROR",

    "message":
        "eth0 link down"
}
```

---

# Supported Failure Categories

Current supported categories:

```
ETHERNET_FAILURE

WIFI_CLIENT_FAILURE
```

Additional categories can be added without changing the pipeline.

---

# Ethernet Failure Detection

Category:

```
ETHERNET_FAILURE
```

---

## Detection Patterns

Examples:

### Link Failure

Pattern:

```
link down
```

Example:

```
eth0: link down
```

Detection:

```
ETHERNET_FAILURE
```

---

### Network Watchdog Timeout

Pattern:

```
NETDEV WATCHDOG
```

Example:

```
NETDEV WATCHDOG timeout
```

Detection:

```
ETHERNET_FAILURE
```

---

### Interface Reset

Patterns:

```
interface reset

driver reset

adapter reset
```

Detection:

```
ETHERNET_FAILURE
```

---

# WiFi Client Failure Detection

Category:

```
WIFI_CLIENT_FAILURE
```

---

## Authentication Failure

Patterns:

```
authentication failed

auth failure

802.1x failure
```

Example:

```
wlan0 authentication failed
```

Detection:

```
WIFI_CLIENT_FAILURE
```

---

## WPA Handshake Failure

Patterns:

```
handshake timeout

WPA failed

4-way handshake failed
```

Example:

```
wpa handshake timeout
```

Detection:

```
WIFI_CLIENT_FAILURE
```

---

## Association Failure

Patterns:

```
association failed

unable to associate

connect timeout
```

Detection:

```
WIFI_CLIENT_FAILURE
```

